cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper presents an automated method for soil mapping using an outdoor mobile robot.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes using Kriging variance as a reward function for robotic exploration, which involves machine learning techniques.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a possible category as the mobile robot may use visual sensors to navigate and collect data.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper proposes using Gaussian process regression (Kriging) for soil mapping.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper involves designing a system for automated soil mapping with a mobile robot.
